<ce:para>The photovoltaics industry produces systems to convert sunlight to electricity and has been growing 20-30% annually for the past several years. The current supply of affordable solar-grade silicon threatens to limit this growth, and new processing technology is needed to increase supply and lower cost. A discussion covers developing models for scale-up and process control design of fluidized bed silicon production; variables influencing the productive operation of the reactor; use of inventory control theory to the process model; sensitivity and prescribe operating conditions; and determining size control requirements for productive operation of a commercial fluidized bed reactor. This is an abstract of a paper presented at the 2006 AIChE Annual Meeting (San Francisco, CA 11/12-17/2006).</ce:para>
